{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BCDjFACvSVwtDZF6BBDddD","type":"tool_result","content":"22:## Project Context Analysis\n52:## Starter Template Evaluation\n73:## Core Architectural Decisions\n100:| `circuit-breaker` | Score-based stagnation detection, score history tracking | FR32-35 |\n103:**Rationale:** 7 modules, each 100-200 LOC. Feedback loop (FR29-30) is part of `workflow-engine` — it's loop logic, not a separate concern. CLI commands (`init`, `run`, `validate`, `status`) are thin wrappers calling these modules. Observability (FR36-37) is a cross-cutting concern handled by trace ID injection in `agent-dispatch`, not a separate module.\n196:7. `circuit-breaker` — depends on evaluator verdicts\n201:- `circuit-breaker` depends on `workflow-state` (reads score history)\n204:## Implementation Patterns & Consistency Rules\n274:## Project Structure & Boundaries\n317:│   │   ├── circuit-breaker.ts            # Score-based stagnation detection (TS rewrite)\n449:- 7 core modules in `src/lib/` (workflow-parser, agent-resolver, workflow-engine, agent-dispatch, evaluator, circuit-breaker, workflow-state)\n465:| FR32-35 (Circuit Breaker) | circuit-breaker |\n466:| FR36-37 (Observability) | agent-dispatch (trace IDs) |\n467:| FR38-41 (CLI) | commands/*.ts |\n496:        circuit-breaker: evaluate stagnation\n501:## Architecture Validation Results\n524:- Implementation sequence defined (state → parser → resolver → dispatch → engine → evaluator → circuit-breaker)\n596:3. New modules in dependency order (state → parser → resolver → dispatch → engine → evaluator → circuit-breaker)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kwq1jWkHGueReqZtY8JQZo","session_id":"0dddd908-79fb-4621-81f1-f9e1a3ee8324","uuid":"c8f4275f-90d2-4cfc-8c3f-359bb40f06ba","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:56:14.513Z"}
