{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Lnk18APjNUdapiHsSWy8ik","type":"tool_result","content":"370\t### Feedback Loop\n371\t\n372\t- FR29: System injects evaluator findings (specific per-AC failure details with evidence) into the retry task's agent prompt\n373\t- FR30: System filters retry execution to only the stories the evaluator flagged as failed\n374\t- FR31: System executes flow loop steps until all ACs pass or circuit breaker triggers\n375\t\n376\t### Progress & Circuit Breaker\n377\t\n378\t- FR32: System tracks evaluator scores across iterations and detects score stagnation\n379\t- FR33: Circuit breaker triggers when evaluator scores stop improving across consecutive iterations\n380\t- FR34: System reports circuit breaker state with specific remaining failures and score history\n381\t- FR35: User can resume execution after circuit breaker with manual fixes applied\n382\t\n383\t### Observability\n384\t\n385\t- FR36: System generates and injects trace IDs that correlate across iteration → agent prompt → logs → metrics → traces\n386\t- FR37: Evaluator can query observability endpoints (VictoriaLogs, VictoriaMetrics, VictoriaTraces) during verification\n387\t\n388\t### Issue Tracking\n389\t\n390\t- FR38: User can create issues via `codeharness issue create \"title\"` with optional priority and source\n391\t- FR39: System stores issues in `issues.yaml` with id, title, source, priority, and status\n392\t- FR40: System reads both `sprint-status.yaml` (stories) and `issues.yaml` (issues) during workflow execution\n393\t- FR41: Issues use the same status values and execution path as stories — the engine treats them uniformly\n394\t- FR42: Retro workflow findings tagged as actionable are automatically added to issues.yaml\n395\t\n396\t### CLI Commands\n397\t\n398\t- FR43: User can run `codeharness init` to detect stack, generate default workflow, and set up the project\n399\t- FR44: User can run `codeharness run` to execute the workflow"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kwq1jWkHGueReqZtY8JQZo","session_id":"0dddd908-79fb-4621-81f1-f9e1a3ee8324","uuid":"3a0bced8-7e22-4b58-8a36-52c33aee156e","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:56:36.301Z"}
