{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WXZRtBrz9oVbLLgmg1gugU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here is a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Files created:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/circuit-breaker.ts` — Pure computation module (~55 LOC) exporting `CircuitBreakerDecision` discriminated union type and `evaluateProgress()` function. Detects score stagnation when `passed` count does not increase between the last two iterations.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/circuit-breaker.test.ts` — 16 unit tests covering all acceptance criteria: stagnation detection, progress detection, insufficient history, remainingFailures, scoreHistory, edge cases (all-unknown, zero-to-zero, single AC), type discrimination, and performance (<5ms for 20 scores).\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — Added import of `evaluateProgress` from `circuit-breaker.js`. Inserted circuit breaker evaluation after score recording in the loop block. When `halt: true`, updates `circuit_breaker` state with `triggered: true`, `reason`, and `score_history`, then persists state. The existing check at line ~660 already handles the halt by setting phase to `'circuit-breaker'`.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — Added `makeProgressingFailVerdict()` helper. Updated 3 existing tests that used constant fail verdicts (which now trigger stagnation detection) to use increasing `passed` counts across iterations.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module.md` — Status changed to `review`, all tasks marked complete.\n\n**Verification:** `npm run build` passes with zero errors. `npm run test:unit` passes all 4126 tests across 159 test files with zero regressions.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Test regressions from integration:** Three existing workflow-engine tests broke because their mock evaluator returned the same `passed: 1` score every iteration, which the new circuit breaker correctly identified as stagnation. Fixed by adding `makeProgressingFailVerdict()` helper that produces increasing `passed` counts across iterations. This is the correct fix — the tests were implicitly relying on the circuit breaker being a no-op.\n- **remainingFailures is approximate:** Per the story's dev notes, `remainingFailures` returns placeholder indices `[1..failCount]` rather than specific AC numbers, because the engine only stores aggregate `EvaluatorScore` (not per-AC findings). This is documented as a known limitation in the story spec itself.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 5, Edit: 5, Write: 2, Grep: 1, Glob: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit` full suite (~15 lines), `npm run test:unit --reporter=verbose | grep FAIL` (~15 lines), `npm run build` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 5 unique, 6 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2754825e77fc2867 (use SendMessage with to: 'a2754825e77fc2867' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 43526\ntool_uses: 29\nduration_ms: 260388</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0dddd908-79fb-4621-81f1-f9e1a3ee8324","uuid":"91199e71-382b-47e4-a4ca-21448e92d5fd","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:04:14.152Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, te