{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M7cHdPNxRinB1ADy98F7e3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review Complete.**\n\n**Story:** 7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module\n**Status:** verifying\n**Issues Found:** 1 High, 2 Medium, 3 Low\n**Issues Fixed:** 1 High, 2 Medium (all HIGH/MEDIUM fixed)\n\n**What was fixed:**\n- Replaced the mock-mutation-based circuit breaker integration test with a proper test that verifies `evaluateProgress()` is called from within `executeLoopBlock` and correctly sets `circuit_breaker.triggered`, `reason` (`'score-stagnation'`), `score_history`, and `phase` (`'circuit-breaker'`) on the workflow state.\n\n**Verification:**\n- Build: passes (zero errors)\n- Tests: 4126/4126 pass (zero regressions)\n- Coverage: 96.81% overall, all 161 files above 80% per-file floor\n- `circuit-breaker.ts`: 100% coverage\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- HIGH: Integration test for circuit breaker used mock mutation instead of testing the real `evaluateProgress()` code path. The test passed coincidentally because the new code set `triggered = true` before the mock did. Fixed by rewriting the test to verify actual `evaluateProgress()` integration with assertions on `reason`, `score_history`, and `phase`.\n- MEDIUM: Old test comment claimed \"circuit breaker was triggered after dispatchCount>=2\" but the actual behavior is different — `evaluateProgress()` triggers after 2 identical scores, not after dispatch count. Fixed (part of test rewrite).\n- MEDIUM: Mock mutation in the old test was dead code (overwritten by the real `evaluateProgress()` result before the mock could take effect). Fixed (removed mock mutation).\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt):**\n- LOW: Test case \"remainingFailures is empty when all pass but stagnation still detected\" (circuit-breaker.test.ts:109) tests a scenario that cannot occur in production (all-pass verdicts exit the loop before circuit breaker check). Harmless but misleading.\n- LOW: No input validation on `EvaluatorScore` fields (e.g., negative `passed`, `passed > total`). The function trusts upstream producers. Acceptable for a pure computation module.\n- LOW: `remainingFailures` includes `unknown` count as failures (`total - passed`), not just `failed`. Documented in Dev Notes but could surprise consumers.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. `circuit-breaker.ts` at 100%, all files above 80% floor, 96.81% overall.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. Module is correctly designed as a pure leaf function with no I/O, imported only by `workflow-engine.ts`.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 7, Edit: 2, Grep: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit` (~60 lines), `git diff workflow-engine.test.ts` (~80 lines), `npm run build` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 8 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: one extra grep on `src/index.ts` with wrong regex pattern (no matches), immediately corrected"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a184df7438e045ee3 (use SendMessage with to: 'a184df7438e045ee3' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59272\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 369286</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0dddd908-79fb-4621-81f1-f9e1a3ee8324","uuid":"b5943844-7468-48f4-9029-d968d1ebaebe","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:10:56.170Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed 